definition: to send/to give as a present
to deliver/to carry/to give (as a present)/to present (with)/to see off/to send
to/for/for the benefit of/to give/to allow/to do sth (for sb)/(grammatical equivalent of 被)/(grammatical equivalent of 把)/(sentence intensifier)

sentences.english: Sends the encrypted session key to the server.
sentences.chinese: 将加密的会话密钥发送给服务器。

sentences.english: A book was given to her as a birthday present.
sentences.chinese: 她哥哥送给她一本书作为生日礼品。

sentences.english: So, WCG sends full support and cheering to our best gamers.
sentences.chinese: 现在，WCG将支持和鼓励送给你们。

sentences.english: The boy was apprenticed to a bricklayer.
sentences.chinese: 那男孩子被送给一个泥瓦匠当学徒。

sentences.english: Below gave everyone a good feeling villages light rock song.
sentences.chinese: 下面送给大家一首好听的乡村轻摇滚感觉的歌。

sentences.english: My girls, will you give them your breakfast as a Christmas present?
sentences.chinese: 姑娘们，你们愿意把早餐送给他们做圣诞礼物吗？

sentences.english: Xiao Wang gave his wife a bouquet of roses for their wedding anniversary.
sentences.chinese: 小王在结婚纪念日送给妻子一束玫瑰花。

sentences.english: Lan Yangyang sent the letter to Hui Tailang by mistake yesterday.
sentences.chinese: 昨天懒羊羊把信错送给了灰太狼。

sentences.english: We have today for warded you our new catalogue.
sentences.chinese: 我们今天已将新目录发送给你们了。

sentences.english: A girl took pictures of the flowers which got from her boyfriend .
sentences.chinese: 一个女孩照了几张关于他男友送给她的花的照片。

sentences.english: Send to my PMB for any further details.
sentences.chinese: 发送给我的PMB任何进一步的细节。

sentences.english: On his birthday, I gave him some cufflinks as a present.
sentences.chinese: 他生日那天，我送给他了一些袖口作为礼物。

sentences.english: In 1716 he gave it to Peter the Great.
The stars that smile on their cottage send us the same twinkling look.
sentences.chinese: 在他们房上微笑的星辰，送给我们以同样的闪亮。

sentences.english: He handed me a necklace last night.
sentences.chinese: 昨晚他送给我一条项链。

sentences.english: Those flowers and fruits on the tea-table are our presents for you.
sentences.chinese: 桌上的鲜花和水果是我们送给您的礼物。
